    <note type="biography">
        <p>Entomologist. Worked for turkey red cotton dyers in Glasgow and calico printers in Manchester. Then suffered ill health and unemployment before being awarded a grant from the Royal Society of London. Known for his work on Hymenoptera, including his Ray Society monograph on British phytophagous Hymenoptera (1882–92). </p></note>
